    <item>
      <title>Stories from a Defunct Drugstore</title>
      <link>https://sloth.direct/posts/stories-from-a-defunct-drugstore/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 29 Jul 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>sloth@sloth.direct (Sloth)</author>
      <guid>https://sloth.direct/posts/stories-from-a-defunct-drugstore/</guid>
      <description>Rite Aid is officially no more. Working in the retail end was my first real job after high school, so I have a lot of stories. This is a highly unorganized collections of my memories from the store.&#xA;I would like to clarify, up-front and in clear text, that all of these stories do not involve the pharmacy. All names are made up to avoid leaking any personally identifiable information, as Rite Aid was a healthcare corporation.</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>About</title>
      <link>https://sloth.direct/about/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 08 Feb 2025 05:47:31 -0500</pubDate><author>sloth@sloth.direct (Sloth)</author>
      <guid>https://sloth.direct/about/</guid>
      <description>Hello! I&amp;rsquo;m Sloth (he/him), a WNY-based chronic shitposter. I am not a Bills fan, as I value the structural integrity of my tables.&#xA;I&amp;rsquo;ve been around various parts of the internet in various capacities. I was an MMO livestreamer for a very long time, but have recently burned out of the genre. Nowadays, most of my gaming time is spent catching up on all of the long single-player RPGs I&amp;rsquo;ve been neglecting.</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>I Own a French Press Now</title>
      <link>https://sloth.direct/posts/french-press/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 08 Feb 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>sloth@sloth.direct (Sloth)</author>
      <guid>https://sloth.direct/posts/french-press/</guid>
      <description>look at this absolute unit&#xA;Ever since I started living alone, I&amp;rsquo;ve gotten really into coffee. Initially, I started out with an automatic brewing machine and a grinder, which is still extremely useful. If I wake up late and need coffee fast, it does the job!&#xA;Should a miracle occur and I manage to wake up on time, I&amp;rsquo;ll make my morning coffee with my French press. I got inspired to learn how to make higher quality coffee after playing Persona 5 Royal and getting carried on SP sustain by Sojiro&amp;rsquo;s brewing lessons.</description>
    </item>
